=E2=80=99m going to talk about Cecily Brown=E2=80=99s potential role as a p=
illar of the art market. At 55, she=E2=80=99s got a mid-career retrospectiv=
e at the Dallas Museum of Art, a show of new work at Paula Cooper Gallery, =
and a single painting at auction next week with an estimate of $4 million. =
Nearly universally praised, collected by almost everyone who cares about co=
ntemporary art, and preternaturally focused on the potentialities and futur=
e of painting, Brown seems poised to become a market mainstay.

