=99m going to talk about Cecily Brown=E2=80=99s potential role as a pillar =
of the art market. At 55, she=E2=80=99s got a mid-career retrospective at t=
he Dallas Museum of Art, a show of new work at Paula Cooper Gallery, and a =
single painting at auction next week with an estimate of $4 million. Nearly=
 universally praised, collected by almost everyone who cares about contempo=
rary art, and preternaturally focused on the potentialities and future of p=
ainting, Brown seems poised to become a market mainstay.
